data.body:
Sheen wasn't properly explained in Burley's 2012 paper, but [Disney's BRDF Explorer has a reference implementation](https://github.com/wdas/brdf/blob/master/src/brdfs/disney.brdf), according to which sheen simply means the linear interpolation between 1.0 and albedo tint (that is, linear color per luminance) in the amount of sheen tint. Looks like we can simply implement this within the spatial material.

As a side note, Blender seems to have adopted it as-is.

@reduz WDYT?
